class Solution {
    public int maxScore(String s) {
        int ones = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') ones++;
        }
        int maxScore = 0, zeros = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length() - 1; i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '0') zeros++;
            else ones--;
            maxScore = Math.max(maxScore, zeros + ones);
        }
        return maxScore;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string twice: once to count the total number of ones and again to calculate the maximum score by maintaining a running count of zeros on the left and ones on the right. This approach is efficient as it only requires a single pass through the string to calculate the maximum score after the initial count of ones.
